# Skill Paths Must Always Be Relative

When writing or updating any skill (`SKILL.md`), every path reference must be **relative to the workspace root** — never a hardcoded absolute path. This applies to all references, not just scripts.

## Rule

❌ **BAD** — absolute paths, break on any other machine:
```
'/Users/sijaiswal/Sids Brain/scripts/sync-vesta-config.py'
'/Users/sijaiswal/Sids Brain/.cursor/skills/some-skill/SKILL.md'
'/Users/sijaiswal/Sids Brain/Vesta/config/objectives/'
```

✅ **GOOD** — relative paths, portable and shareable:
```
'scripts/sync-vesta-config.py'
'.cursor/skills/some-skill/SKILL.md'
'Vesta/config/objectives/'
```

## Applies To

- External scripts (Python, shell, etc.)
- References to other skill folders or `SKILL.md` files
- Folder paths (input dirs, output dirs, config dirs)
- Shell commands embedded in skills (`cd`, `python3`, file reads/writes)
- `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location` calls
- Notes, footers, and any instructional text that mentions a path

## When cd Is Needed

If the skill must `cd` to the workspace root before running, use the workspace path from the always-applied `sids-brain-location` rule (`/Users/sijaiswal/Sids Brain`) only inside the `cd` command — all subsequent paths in that same command block must be relative.
